description: TEHRAN – Iran held off a fightback from the United Arab Emirates to top Group I of the AFC U23 Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2026 Qualifiers Group I with a 3-2 win on Tuesday.
title: Iran advance to AFC U23 Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2026

description: TEHRAN – Iran has decided to look for ways to allow International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) inspectors back into the country, after it suspended cooperation with the UN nuclear watchdog back in July following U.S.-Israeli attacks on its nuclear sites
title: Iran decides to resume cooperation with IAEA

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian spent much of his time at a conference marking the Islamic Unity Week in Tehran making general remarks about how unity among Muslims is important, and how cohesion will benefit all Muslim nations in the region. At one point though, he took a more firm and straightforward tone, asking regional states to do more than condemnation in addressing Israel’s unchecked violence in the region.
title: Your statements are good, but not enough

description: TEHRAN - Arman-e-Emrooz discussed the quarterly meeting A of the Board of Governors at the International Atomic Energy Agency that stated on Monday, writing: The meeting of the Board of Governors, which is being this month, is one of the most important events of the year in the area of nuclear diplomacy, because its main focus is to review the Iran nuclear file.
title: Meeting with a positive outlook

description: TEHRAN – Iran has unveiled plans for a series of satellite launches in the second half of the current year, underscoring its determination to expand its domestic space program and reduce reliance on foreign technology.
title: Iran unveils multiple satellite launch plans amid push for space self-reliance

description: TEHRAN – Iran and Iraq have formalized a comprehensive 21-point agreement aimed at enhancing cooperation across economic, political, and security sectors.
title: Iran, Iraq sign 21-point cooperation agreement covering economy, security, and politics

description: TEHRAN – Iran has reaffirmed that its missile and defense capabilities are not subject to negotiation, even as it continues diplomatic engagement with Europe and the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) amid heightened tensions over sanctions and nuclear safeguards.
title: We won’t negotiate our missiles: Iran foreign ministry

description: TEHRAN – The convening of the “Second Meeting of Muslim Leaders of BRICS Countries” hosted by Brazil is a turning point in the life of this forum and, beyond that, a pillar in strengthening the BRICS coalition. The consultation and synergy of Muslim leaders within the BRICS framework regarding international crises is not merely desirable, but an absolute necessity.
title: The role of Muslim leaders in strengthening the BRICS coalition

description: TEHRAN – Beijing’s growing dependence on Persian Gulf oil and its aspiration to play mediator in the West Asia disputes collide in the narrow waters of the Strait of Hormuz. As more than 40% of China’s crude shipments flow through this chokepoint, how China maneuvers its ambitions without sparking a direct clash has become a vital barometer of its evolving global role.
title: Strait of Hormuz, China’s imperative for deeper engagement in Persian Gulf

description: TEHRAN – FIFA President Infantino assured the team members of Iran national football team that FIFA will do its utmost to resolve visa-related issues and facilitate the teams’ participation in upcoming tournaments, including the 2026 World Cup.
title: Infantino assures Iran for 2026 World Cup’s participation
